onment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/causal-edges.vitest.ts:\n  Line 566:     it('should break down by relation type', () => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/description/fixtures/017-001-infrastructure-primitives.description.json:\n  Line 3:   \"description\": \"Phase 017 Wave A child packet: infrastructure primitives (~20h, CRITICAL PATH). 5 tasks: T-CNS-01 + T-W1-CNS-04 (canonical save metadata writer, merged PR, 6h, eliminates H-56-1 root cause), T-CGC-01 (extract lib/code-graph/readiness-contract.ts, 4h, prereq for Wave B T-W1-CGC-03), T-W1-HOK-02 (extract hooks/shared-provenance.ts, 4h, prereq for Wave B T-W1-HOK-01 — breaks a cross-runtime transitive import R52-P2-001), T-SCP-01 (collapse 4 local normalizers to canonical, 4h, resolves R1-P1-001 + R4-P1-001 compound), T-EVD-01-prep (rewrap 016 checklist.md evidence markers ')' → ']', 2h, prereq for Wave C T-EVD-01 strict mode). Blocks all downstream Wave B/C/D work. Atomic-ship: G1 (T-CNS-01 + T-W1-CNS-04) MUST land as single PR. Gate: /deep:start-review-loop :auto ×7 emits ZERO new P0/P1.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/hooks-shared-provenance.vitest.ts:\n  Line 49:     it('url-encodes special characters that could break the marker line', () => {\n\n  Line 234:     it('escapes adversarial metadata so forged markers cannot break out', () => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/architecture-cleanup-cycles.vitest.ts:\n  Line 31: describe('F-017-D2-01: StructuralBootstrapContract cycle break', () => {\n\n  Line 54: describe('F-017-D2-02: Community types cycle break', () => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/memory-summaries.vitest.ts:\n  Line 265:       'First sentence about quantum computing breakthroughs.',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/search-fallback-tiered.vitest.ts:\n  Line 69:       break;\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/shadow-scoring-holdout.vitest.ts:\n  Line 902:       // Most recent 2 are improvements, then regression breaks the streak\n\n  Line 919:       // Only w3 is consecutive from the end; w2 breaks the streak\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/token-budget-skip-and-floor.vitest.ts:\n  Line 32:   it('keeps smaller fitting results when the top result overflows (no hard break)', () => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/k-value-judged-sweep.vitest.ts:\n  Line 3: // Tests: NDCG@10, MRR@5, per-intent segmentation, tie-breaking, empty query set, flag OFF\n\n  Line 286:   it('D3-ARG-2: tie-break favors lower K', () => {\n\n  Line 296:     // K=10 and K=20 and K=60 all have 0.7 — tie-break to K=10\n\n  Line 428:   it('D3-SWEEP-ON-8: intent with all-zero NDCG selects lowest K (tie-break)', () => {\n\n  Line 436:     // All NDCG=0 (relevant ID missing) → tie-break to lowest K\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/quality-loop.vitest.ts:\n  Line 53: - Implemented fail-safe logging that never breaks production search\n\n  Line 283:     expect(score.breakdown.triggers).toBe(1.0);\n\n  Line 284:     expect(score.breakdown.anchors).toBe(1.0);\n\n  Line 285:     expect(score.breakdown.coherence).toBe(1.0);\n\n  Line 294:     expect(score.breakdown.triggers).toBe(0);\n\n  Line 307:     if (score.breakdown.triggers === 1.0 && score.breakdown.anchors === 1.0 &&\n\n  Line 308:         score.breakdown.budget === 1.0 && score.breakdown.coherence === 1.0) {\n\n  Line 487:   it('reports actual attempts when early break stops further retries', () => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/fixtures/runtime-fixtures.ts:\n  Line 78:       break;\n\n  Line 82:       break;\n\n  Line 85:       break;\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/memory-crud-extended.vitest.ts:\n  Line 995:   it('EXT-S2: Stats includes status breakdown', async () => {\n","metadata":{"matches":91,"truncated":false},"title":"RetryOptions|early-abort|break","time":{"start":1781718623098,"end":1781718623122}},"id":"prt_ed6b49fe6001H4sjHq0hrkLZmT","sessionID":"ses_1294e112dffeF8UlfEsNhSrzCb","messageID":"msg_ed6b473fa001svcvc24HvH0Qke"}}
